(Handwritten) *Diapensi*

Plants of ALABAMA, U.S.A.

*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt

CLEBURNE CO.: ca. 8 air mi SW of Heflin, along W
side of route 431, 2.5 mi S of junction of routes 431
and I-20.

Dry-mesic forest on slope above road; forest dominated
by *Quercus*, *Pinus*, *Nyssa sylvatica*, *Acer rubrum*,
*Cornus florida*; thick leaf litter; frequent.

Robert F.C. Naczi 5478                      23 May 1996
